genresAdvancedInfo.name: ilocano pop
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Ilocano Pop is a popular music genre from the Philippines that originated in the Ilocos region. It features upbeat melodies and catchy rhythms, often incorporating traditional instruments such as the guitar and the kulintang. Ilocano Pop songs are typically sung in the Ilocano language and cover a variety of themes, including love, nostalgia, and social issues. The genre has gained popularity in recent years, with many Ilocano Pop artists achieving mainstream success.
